sql structured queary language 

- a software that is used to manage our database is called data dbms (database management system)


where database is classfied into 
1. rationl database 
2.non rational database 


rational database : always store  the data in tablular formate ( ex  mysql postgrs sql )

non rational database : thre are data without no tables ( mangobd )


sql used to perform some operation : CRUD

create 
read
update
delete


sql commend types :

ddl :data defination language : defines data and schema it have commends like  create , drop , alter , rename,truncate 

dql :data queary language : used to view the data  and cmd is view data 

dml : data manuplucation language :change and manuplaicate the data - cmd is used are insert and update , delete data 

dcl : data control language : manage permission and access 

tcl trancation control lauguages :handdles the transations ( commit , rollback ) advance db operation 



 sql  data types :

CHAR  : name , city , charcter   and (0 to 255) size can be stored  
    - it take the place complectly evn the place is full 



VARCHAR :  varchar is same as  char can store the name , place ,charctera 
    - can store at given length ( o to 255) 
    - it store  according to the place it fits and remaining place will be left 


BLOB : can store up to 65535 , can store binary upto large object 






numerical type :

INT :  can store  integers  vulues both   +ve ,-ve  values 

TINY INT : integers between -128 to 127 

bit :BIT(1) → {0, 1}

     BIT(2) → {00, 01, 10, 11}

    BIT(3) → {000, 001, 010, 011, 100, 101, 110, 111


FLOAT :  float is noting but decimal values , pression upto 23 digits 

DOUBLE : means large decimal values 



OTHER TYPES :

BOOL : is nothing but true or false o, 1 or 0 , use tiny int in mysql 

DATE :  year , month , day 


SIGNED OR UNSIGNED :

signed : signed allowes  negative and positive numbers(defalult )

unsigned : unsigned in allow only positive numbers ( increasing range )









